for%20them%20to%20work%20at%20its%20stores%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-new-ceo-brian-niccol-made-millions-in-months-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECEO%20Brian%20Niccol%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20after%20Starbucks%20reported%20its%20second-quarter%20earnings%20Tuesday.%20Starbucks%20is%20also%20using%20a%20new%20algorithm%20to%20determine%20the%20order%20in%20which%20store%20employees%20make%20drinks%2C%20avoiding%20long%20wait%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarbucks%20is%20planning%20to%20roll%20out%20the%20new%20approach%2C%20called%20the%20Green%20Apron%20Service%20model%2C%20starting%20next%20month.%20The%20goal%20is%20to%20have%20it%20in%20about%20a%20third%20of%20its%20US%20locations%20by%20the%20end%20of%20its%202025%20fiscal%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20finding%20that%20investments%20in%20labor%20rather%20than%20equipment%20are%20more%20effective%26quot%3B%20at%20getting%20customers%20their%20orders%20and%20growing%20sales%2C%20Niccol%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarbucks'%20shares%20were%20trading%20nearly%207%25%20lower%20after%20hours%20on%20Tuesday%20after%20the%20company%20outlined%20its%20plans%20to%20invest%20in%20employee%20hours.%20The%20company%20reported%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-sales-down-ceo-says-doesnt-yet-reflect-progress-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecond-quarter%20earnings%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20were%20slightly%20below%20analysts'%20estimates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20investment%20in%20employee%20hours%20is%20a%20departure%20from%20Starbucks'%20approach%20to%20staffing%20stores%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20Niccol%20joined%20the%20company%20as%20CEO%20and%20chairman%20in%20September%2C%20the%20chain%20had%20cut%20hours%2C%20leading%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-worker-long-wait-times-down-to-staffing-mobile-orders-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%2