t%2C%20and%20widening%20social%20and%20economic%20inequities%20%E2%80%94%20that%20threaten%20global%20stability.%20A%20shift%20toward%20a%20greener%20economy%20is%20critical%20to%20addressing%20the%20climate%20crisis%20and%20promoting%20sustainable%20development.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20transformation%20requires%20innovative%2C%20inclusive%20solutions%20that%20create%20jobs%20and%20promote%20environmental%20stewardship.%20At%20the%20heart%20of%20this%20transition%20are%20women-led%20enterprises%2C%20which%20play%20a%20vital%20role%20in%20driving%20change%20by%20creating%20green%20jobs%2C%20reducing%20carbon%20emissions%2C%20and%20building%20resilience.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20their%20essential%20contributions%2C%20women%20often%20remain%20overlooked%20in%20traditional%20economic%20models%2C%20perpetuating%20a%20gender%20gap%20that%20hampers%20sustainable%20progress.%20Emerging%20sectors%20like%20renewable%20energy%20and%20green%20technology%20are%20still%20largely%20male-dominated%2C%20leaving%20women%20underrepresented%20in%20leadership%2C%20employment%2C%20and%20entrepreneurship.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20green%20economy%20offers%20a%20unique%20opportunity%20to%20empower%20women%2C%20especially%20in%20rural%20and%20underserved%20communities%2C%20by%20enabling%20them%20to%20lead%20enterprises%20that%20address%20both%20climate%20challenges%20and%20economic%20disparities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20for%20example%2C%20women-led%20green%20enterprises%20are%20becoming%20powerful%20agents%20of%20change%2C%20improving%20resilience%20in%20areas%20facing%20environmental%20degradation%2C%20water%20scarcity%2C%20and%20pollution.%20Organisations%20like%20Development%20Alternatives%20(DA)%20work%20alongside%20vulnerable%20communities%2C%20empowering%20women%20through%20skill%20development%20and%20economic%20opportunities%2C%20which%20ripple%20out%20to%20improve%20education%2C%20healthcare%2C%20and%20household%20well-being.%